My first time trying it and wow, I am not disappointed at all. I got the Number 2 based on the guy's suggestion, which has just an amazing mix of crunchy with the chicken, and savory. No one else was there when I was, but please don't let that fool you and just go in!
The Number One is a great place to start if you're new. Great food and great service.

Friendly staff, got the Cheese Steak Wrap, was loaded with steak, cheese and wait for it tater tots. Who would have thought of doing that, it's like putting the hash browns with the eggs in a egg sandwich. Which they actually have with their breakfast wraps, any one of those has eggs and tots together.  I am sure they are as tasty as the Cheese Steak.  Also got some waffle fries as well, one can never have too much potatos, could have gotten some more tots but I thought I would not put all the potatos in one basket. They  good, a lilttle greesy though, don't think the oil was hot enough to seal the fries while cooking, not a big thing.  They are open really late for the bar crowd. The location is primed for that on Milwaukee. So if you are out late and hungery this place will have ya back.
Amazing Buffalo chicken wrap. Only wish I had found this place sooner!
the food is very good
Had the bacon chicken and swiss wrap tasted pretty good, the portion is huge which made it worth the price.  Restaurant was clean.
This is an amazing place to go to when your in need of comfort food. This place will hopefully one day become a wicker park mainstay.

This place has a great staff and fantastic drunk/hangover food. The lack of customers doesn't do it justice... i think the problem is their misleading "clean and healthy"-looking storefront aesthetic. My Son brought home one of these wraps for me and it was...Amazing!  He had told me about Conrad's and I was a little skeptical, it's a very different concept. But it was sooo tasty!  I don't remember what mine was called but my wrap had eggs, sausage and french toast in it. The best part is that I didn't know what was in it, so  it put a smile on my face when I figured it out. Don't ask me how, but it totally works - all I can say is you gotta try it for yourself!
